# Ship Loop (stageverify)

After **any** substantive code or config change in this repo, complete the ship loop before declaring done.

## Default deploy policy

**Default deploy policy:** For frontend-only StageVerify changes that pass validation, agents should commit, push, deploy gh-pages, and run production verification unless Dan explicitly says not to deploy (e.g. "do not deploy", "hold deploy", "local only", "commit and push only", or work is WIP on a branch). Backend deploys, Firestore rules, Cloud Functions, Gmail sync/watch behavior, and security-sensitive changes still require **explicit Dan approval** before any production deploy — agents must ask first.

**Authoritative:** This file is the source of truth for commit, push, gh-pages deploy, production verification, backend guardrails, and skip triggers. Other rules cross-reference here; do not duplicate full policy elsewhere.

### Frontend/UI agents (deploy default)

- **Default:** frontend-only changes that pass validation → commit, push, deploy gh-pages, prod verification — unless Dan explicitly says not to deploy.
- **Ask first:** Firestore rules, Cloud Functions, Gmail sync/watch, backend/security/data, or other risky production behavior — require Dan's explicit approval before any deploy.

Do not hesitate on normal frontend/UI ship; do not auto-deploy backend or security-sensitive paths.

## Sequence (frontend / UI default)

1. **Validate** — `npm run build` clean; local Playwright / `verify:*` for affected routes (per `composer-orchestrator.mdc`). If any test fails, **do not deploy** — fix and re-run.
2. `git status` — stage **only** task-related files.
3. Conventional commit (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`).
4. `git push origin main` — must succeed.
5. **`npm run deploy`** — GitHub Pages (`https://lgarage.github.io/stageverify`); must succeed or report failure clearly. Deploy script must confirm Pages build status **`built`** (not just gh-pages branch push).
6. **Production verification** — after deploy, run matching prod checks (see below). If gh-pages is not yet serving the new bundle, wait **15 seconds** and retry once.
7. **Report** — live URL `https://lgarage.github.io/stageverify` and deployed commit hash (`git rev-parse HEAD` after push).

Rules-only or docs-only tasks that do not change the frontend bundle: commit + push only; skip steps 5–7 unless Dan asks to deploy.

## When to deploy (gh-pages)

Deploy by default when the change is **frontend-only** (UI, client routing, static assets, verify scripts that exercise the deployed bundle) **and** validation in step 1 passed.

Do **not** auto-deploy gh-pages when:

- Dan explicitly skips deploy (see **When to skip**).
- Build or Playwright / `verify:*` failed.
- The change is backend-only, security-sensitive, or touches Firestore rules / Cloud Functions / Gmail production behavior — **ask Dan before any deploy** (frontend or backend).

## Production verification

After `npm run deploy`, run prod checks for routes touched by the change:

| Script | Prod invocation |
|--------|-----------------|
| Any script with `:prod` suffix | e.g. `npm run verify:pickup:prod` |
| `verify:delivery-consistency` | `STAGEVERIFY_BASE_URL=https://lgarage.github.io/stageverify npm run verify:delivery-consistency` |
| `verify:phase5-email` | `STAGEVERIFY_BASE_URL=https://lgarage.github.io/stageverify npm run verify:phase5-email` |
| `verify:dispatcher-nav` | `STAGEVERIFY_BASE_URL=https://lgarage.github.io/stageverify npm run verify:dispatcher-nav` |

Run only scripts relevant to the shipped change. Retry once after **15s** if failure looks like gh-pages propagation lag.

## Backend and security guardrails (explicit approval required)

Agents must **not** auto-run these without Dan's explicit approval in the session:

| Action | Command / behavior |
|--------|-------------------|
| Firestore rules | `firebase deploy --only firestore:rules --project stageverify-db` |
| Cloud Functions | `firebase deploy --only functions --project stageverify-db` (or scoped function names) |
| Gmail watch / sync / inbound auto-ingest | Any CF or config that enables production email sync |
| Other backend / security deploys | Auth changes, secrets, public unauthenticated writes, schema migrations |

When an approved backend deploy is required, run it in the **same session** as the related change, after any Sonnet security gate (`model-audit-gate.mdc`). Report what was deployed separately from gh-pages.

## When to skip

Skip commit, push, and/or deploy when:

- Dan explicitly says hold off, do not deploy, hold deploy, local only, commit and push only, or similar.
- Work is WIP on a branch (not `main`).
- Validation failed (build, Playwright, or relevant `verify:*`).
- Change is risky backend/security/data and Dan has not approved deploy.

Partial skip: Dan may allow commit + push without gh-pages — honor that; do not deploy.

## Overrides

This workspace rule **overrides** the generic Cursor user rule “only commit when requested.” In stageverify, ship (including default gh-pages deploy for passing frontend work) unless Dan says otherwise.

Multitask / tight-scope prompts that say "no deploy unless required" apply **only to that task's stated scope** — they do not override this default for normal frontend/UI work.

## Done gate

Do **not** declare done until:

- Push succeeded, and
- For frontend/UI work: deploy succeeded (or deploy failure is clearly reported with next steps), prod verification ran when applicable, and live URL + commit hash are reported.

Backend-only or rules-only work: done after push (and approved backend deploy if applicable) — no gh-pages deploy required unless the bundle changed.

## UI changes

- Playwright verify **before** commit (build + local verify per `composer-orchestrator.mdc`).
- After deploy, run `:prod` or `STAGEVERIFY_BASE_URL=…` prod scripts when they exist for affected routes.

## PROJECT_STATUS

When a feature ships, include `PROJECT_STATUS/CURRENT_STATE.md`, `docs/project_state.md`, and `docs/roadmap.md` (when applicable) in the **same** commit as the feature code.
